properties.headline: High Wind Warning issued January 1 at 2:34AM MST until January 1 at 11:00AM MST by NWS Cheyenne WY
properties.description:
...Strong Winds Expected For Wind Prone Locations Into This
Evening...

* WHAT...West winds 30 to 45 mph with gusts up to 65 mph.

* WHERE...Northern Carbon and northern Albany Counties to
include Muddy Gap...Shirley Basin and Medicine Bow.

* WHEN...Through 11 AM today.

* IMPACTS...Mainly to transportation. Travel will be hazardous
for light weight and high profile vehicles, including camping
and tractor trailers. There will be an elevated blow over risk
along Highway 287 north of Rawlins to Muddy Gap as well as
north to south oriented roads near Seminoe Park.
properties.instruction:
Monitor the latest forecasts and warnings for updates on this
situation. Fasten loose objects or shelter objects in a safe
location prior to the onset of winds.

A High Wind Warning means a hazardous high wind event is expected
or occurring. Sustained wind speeds of at least 40 mph or gusts
of 58 mph or more can lead to property damage.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 11 AM MST THIS MORNING
